snippet: The High Line at the Rail Yards opens on Sept. 21, with lush plantings, picnic tables, a seesaw for children and a wild, untouched section as you head west.
abstract: Final section of New York City's elevated park, High Line, is set to open at Rail Yards; plants at section are being kept wild and untouched, with rusted rails and weathered ties, surrounding picnic tables and children's seesaw accessible after crossing 11th Avenue bridge.
lead_paragraph: The High Line at the Rail Yards opens on Sept. 21, with lush plantings, picnic tables, a seesaw for children and a wild, untouched section as you head west.

headline.seo: Unruly Final Section of High Line to Open
headline.main: Upstairs, a Walk on the Wild Side
